<!--
    ServiceNow Update Set record-definition for the `sys_dictionary` row that
    declares the `number` Auto-number String field on the `x_[scope]_case`
    custom table inside the scoped application `x_[scope]_case_management`.

    Per AAP Section 0.5.7 (Data-Model Mapping verbatim):
        Field   Type            Constraints
        number  Auto-number     Read-only, format CASE0000001

    Per AAP Section 0.7.4 (Other User-Provided Rules):
        "Auto-numbering format: the case `number` field MUST use format
         CASE0000001 (7-digit zero-padded) and be Read-only."

    This dictionary entry ONLY declares that the `number` field exists on the
    parent table. The auto-population logic (prefix `CASE`, padding 7,
    starting value, format `CASE0000001`) is configured by a separate
    sys_number record in `../numbers/sys_number_x_[scope]_case.xml`. The
    parent table record `../tables/x_[scope]_case.xml` connects this field
    to that auto-number generator via its `<number_ref>` element (which
    already resolves to `x_[scope]_case_number` via `source` lookup). No
    redundant linkage is authored here.

    Semantic source-side reference (read-only, NOT byte-for-byte ported):
      - acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin/src/main/java/
        com/armedia/acm/plugins/casefile/model/CaseFile.java line 130-132:
            @Column(name = "cm_case_number")
            @AcmSequence(sequenceName = "caseNumberSequence")
            private String caseNumber;
        ArkCase's `caseNumber` String field on the `acm_case_file` JPA entity
        was sequence-generated by the @AcmSequence annotation backed by a
        dedicated sequence row in the `acm_sequence` table. The ServiceNow
        target replaces both the @Column declaration AND the @AcmSequence
        generator with this dictionary entry plus the sibling sys_number
        record - a single declarative low-code equivalent of the JPA pair.
      - The field name is `number` (lowercase, NOT `caseNumber`, NOT
        `case_number`) per AAP Section 0.5.7 verbatim. This is the
        conventional ServiceNow auto-number field name across the platform
        (incident.number, change_request.number, sc_request.number, etc.).

    Constraints honored (AAP Sections 0.7.1, 0.7.2, 0.7.4):
      - Scope-namespace exclusivity: `<name>` resolves to `x_[scope]_case`
        within the scoped application, and `<sys_scope>` / `<sys_package>`
        bind THIS dictionary record to the same scope by `source` attribute
        lookup. NO global-scope writes - the OOB tables `task`, `incident`,
        `sys_user`, etc. are never modified.
      - Zero hardcoded cross-reference sys_ids: the `<sys_scope>` and
        `<sys_package>` text-node values resolve by scope source name
        (`x_[scope]_case_management`), not by literal sys_id. The `<sys_id>`
        text-node value is THIS record's own deterministic primary key
        (MD5 of the canonical field identifier `x_[scope]_case.number`)
        and is NOT a reference to any other record.
      - The literal `[scope]` placeholder is preserved per AAP convention;
        the PDI auto-assigns the actual scope id at App Engine Studio
        creation time.
      - Read-only at the dictionary level (`<read_only>true</read_only>`)
        per AAP Section 0.7.4 verbatim. No internal user, agent, or
        manager may directly edit this field; only the platform's
        auto-number generator may populate it on insert.
      - Mandatory at the dictionary level is FALSE because the auto-number
        generator populates the field server-side on insert; setting
        mandatory to true would block any GlideRecord.insert() that does
        not explicitly include a `number`, contradicting the
        auto-population semantic. (The platform itself ALWAYS guarantees
        a value will be generated.)
      - Unique at the dictionary level is TRUE: belt-and-suspenders against
        any future code path that might attempt to bypass the auto-number
        generator and assign a duplicate value. The platform's auto-number
        generator already guarantees uniqueness; this adds an
        index-backed enforcement layer.
      - Default-sort at the dictionary level is TRUE: ServiceNow list views
        on `x_[scope]_case` will default to sorting by `number`. With
        descending sort, the most recently created cases (with the highest
        sequential numbers) appear at the top of the list - matching
        agent / manager workflow expectations.
      - max_length 40 is generous: the prescribed format `CASE0000001`
        consumes 11 characters; the additional headroom accommodates
        future format extensions (e.g., `CASE-2026-0000001` = 17 chars,
        `CASE-DEPT-NN-0000001` = 20 chars) without a schema migration.
      - choice 0 = free-form String (no choice list), as required for an
        auto-numbered identifier.
      - No reference target: this is a String field, not a Reference field.
        All `<reference*>` elements are empty.
      - No PII: the field stores only synthetic auto-generated identifiers
        (`CASE0000001`, etc.); no real names, email addresses, or
        organizational identifiers are derived from or stored in this
        column.

    Cross-references (AAP Section 0.5.2 dependency ordering):
      - This record MUST load AFTER `../tables/x_[scope]_case.xml`
        (parent table), since `<name>x_[scope]_case</name>` references
        the table by name.
      - This record SHOULD load alongside or before
        `../numbers/sys_number_x_[scope]_case.xml`. The auto-number
        generator's `<table>` field references the parent table by name,
        and the parent table's `<number_ref>` already targets the
        sys_number record by `source` attribute - so the dictionary
        entry, the sys_number, and the table all resolve correctly
        regardless of strict ordering once their `name` columns exist.
      - This record MUST load BEFORE the consumers that read or write
        the `number` column:
          * ../portal/rest/sys_ws_definition_x_[scope]_case_submit.xml
            (returns the auto-generated number to the requester)
          * ../portal/rest/sys_ws_definition_x_[scope]_case_status_lookup.xml
            (queries cases by number and returns status/subject/opened_date)
          * ../seed-data/cases/x_[scope]_case_demo_*.xml (synthetic demo
            cases that may pre-assign numbers `CASE0000001` through
            `CASE0000010` during seeding)
-->
